Introduced Version
HOUSE BILL No. 1328
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 16-18-2; IC 16-21-20.
Synopsis: Charges for hospital administered drugs. Prohibits a
hospital from billing for an administered drug an amount that exceeds
the lesser of the following: (1) 120% of the Medicare reimbursement
rate for the administered drug. (2) The amount the hospital bills for the
administered drug on June 30, 2026. Creates an exception. Requires a
hospital to update the Medicare reimbursement rate for an administered
drug on January 1 and July 1 of each year.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
McGuire, Barrett
January 6, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Public Health.
