HOUSE BILL No. 1328
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
health.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 16-18-2-2.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
3 1, 2026]: Sec. 2.5. "Administered drug", for purposes of
4 IC 16-21-20, has the meaning set forth in IC 16-21-20-2.
5 SECTION 2. IC 16-18-2-223.9 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
6 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
7 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 223.9. "Medicare reimbursement
8 rate", for purposes of IC 16-21-20, has the meaning set forth in
9 IC 16-21-20-3.
10 SECTION 3. IC 16-21-20 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
11 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
12 JULY 1, 2026]:
13 Chapter 20. Billing for Administered Drugs
14 Sec. 1. This chapter does not apply to the following:
15 (1) A critical access hospital that meets the criteria under 42
16 CFR 485.601 through 42 CFR 485.647.
17 (2) The Medicaid program.
2026 IN 1328—LS 6862/DI 147

2
1 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "administered drug" means a
2 drug delivered to the body of a person by injection, infusion,
3 ingestion, or any other means.
4 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "Medicare reimbursement rate"
5 refers to the rate the federal Centers for Medicare and Medicaid
6 Services pays for a drug or biological product under Medicare Part
7 B.
8 Sec. 4. (a) Except as provided in subsection (b), a hospital
9 licensed under this article may not submit a bill for an
10 administered drug in an amount that exceeds the lesser of the
11 following:
12 (1) One hundred twenty percent (120%) of the Medicare
13 reimbursement rate for the administered drug.
14 (2) The amount the hospital bills for the administered drug on
15 June 30, 2026.
16 (b) If the Medicare reimbursement rate for an administered
17 drug increases, a hospital may submit a bill for an administered
18 drug that exceeds the amount described in subsection (a)(2) only in
19 an amount that does not exceed the percentage increase in the
20 Medicare reimbursement rate applied to the amount billed by the
21 hospital for the drug on June 30, 2026.
22 Sec. 5. A hospital shall update the Medicare reimbursement rate
23 for each administered drug on:
24 (1) January 1; and
25 (2) July 1;
26 of each year based on the Medicare reimbursement rate published
27 by the federal Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services for the
28 most recent calendar quarter.
